Rockstar Games’ Red Dead Redemption 2 is just around the corner, set to be released on 26 October 2018. With a week to go, Rockstar released a new trailer for the game, and also confirmed that players can start preloading the game on PlayStation 4 and Xbox One. A week is a long time to download the game, but the total download size for the title put this into perspective. Rockstar’s support page clarifies that the total download size for Xbox One is 107GB, and 99GB for PlayStation 4. Additionally, PlayStation 4 users will require an extra 50GB for the installation process. You can watch the new trailer for Red Dead Redemption 2 below. <span data-mce-type="bookmark" style="display: inline-block; width: 0px; overflow: hidden; line-height: 0;" class="mce_SELRES_start">﻿</span>